LC:LAM.2.16.12" \w* \w  is the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.16.13" \w* \w  for which we have waited .  |strong="6960" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.16.14" \w* \w  We have lived  |strong="4672" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.16.15" \w* \w  to see it ! ”  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.16.16" \w* \v 17 \w  The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.2" \w* \w  has done  |strong="6213" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.1" \w* \w  what  |strong="834" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.3" \w* \w  He planned ;  |strong="2161" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.4" \w* \w  He has accomplished  |strong="1214" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.5" \w* \w  His decree ,  |strong="565" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.6" \w* \w  which  |strong="834" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.7" \w* \w  He ordained  |strong="6680" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.8" \w* \w  in days  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.9" \w* \w  of old ;  |strong="6924" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.10" \w* \w  He has overthrown you  |strong="2040" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.11" \w* \w  without  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.12" \w* \w  pity .  |strong="2550" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.13" \w* \w  He has let the enemy  |strong="341" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.16" \w* \w  gloat  |strong="8055" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.14" \w* \w  over you  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.15" \w* \w  and exalted  |strong="7311" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.17" \w* \w  the horn  |strong="7161" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.18" \w* \f + \fr 2.17 \ft Or "the strength" \f* \w  of your foes .  |strong="6862" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.17.19" \w* \v 18 \w  The hearts [of the people]  |strong="3820" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.2" \w* \w  cry out  |strong="6817" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.1" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.3" \w* \w  the Lord .  |strong="136" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.4" \w* \f + \fr 2.18 \ft Literally "Their heart cries out to the Lord." \f* \w  O wall  |strong="2346" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.5" \w* \w  of the Daughter  |strong="1323" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.6" \w* \w  of Zion ,  |strong="6726" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.7" \w* \w  let your tears  |strong="1832" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.10" \w* \w  run down  |strong="3381" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.8" \w* \w  like a river  |strong="5158" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.9" \w* \w  day  |strong="3119" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.11" \w* \w  and night .  |strong="3915" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.12" \w* \w  Give  |strong="5414" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.14" \w* \w  yourself  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.16" \w* \w  no  |strong="408" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.13" \w* \w  relief ,  |strong="6314" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.15" \w* \w  and your eyes  |strong="5869" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.20" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="1323" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.19" \w* \w  no  |strong="408" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.17" \w* \w  rest .  |strong="1826" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.18.18" \w* \v 19 \w  Arise ,  |strong="6965" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.1" \w* \w  cry out  |strong="7442" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.2" \w* \w  in the night  |strong="3915" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.3" \w* \w  from the first  |strong="7218" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.4" \w* \w  watch of the night .  |strong="821" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.5" \w* \f + \fr 2.19 \ft That is, between six and nine at night \f* \w  Pour out  |strong="8210" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.6" \w* \w  your heart  |strong="3820" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.8" \w* \w  like water  |strong="4325" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.7" \w* \w  in  |strong="5227" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.9" \w* \w  the presence  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.10" \w* \w  of the Lord .  |strong="136" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.11" \w* \w  Lift up  |strong="5375" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.12" \w* \w  your hands  |strong="3709" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.14" \w* \w  to Him  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.13" \w* \w  for  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.15" \w* \w  the lives  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.16" \w* \w  of your children  |strong="5768" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.17" \w* \w  who are fainting  |strong="5848" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.18" \w* \w  from hunger  |strong="7458" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.19" \w* \w  on the corner  |strong="7218" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.20" \w* \w  of every  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.21" \w* \w  street .  |strong="2351" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.19.22" \w* \v 20 \w  Look ,  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.1" \w* \w  O LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.2" \w* \w  and consider :  |strong="5027" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.3" \w* \w  Whom  |strong="4310" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.4" \w* \w  have You [ever] treated  |strong="5953" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.5" \w* \w  like this ?  |strong="3541" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.6" \w* \w  Should  |strong="518" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.7" \w* \w  women  |strong="802" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.9" \w* \w  eat  |strong="398" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.8" \w* \w  their offspring ,  |strong="6529" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.10" \w* \w  the infants  |strong="5768" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.11" \w* \w  they have nurtured ?  |strong="2949" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.12" \w* \w  Should priests  |strong="3548" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.17" \w* \w  and prophets  |strong="5030" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.18" \w* \w  be killed  |strong="2026" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.14" \w* \w  in the sanctuary  |strong="4720" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.15" \w* \w  of the Lord  |strong="136" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.16" \w* \w  . . . ?  |strong="518" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.20.13" \w* \v 21 \w  Both young  |strong="5288" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.4" \w* \w  and old  |strong="2205" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.5" \w* \w  lie together  |strong="7901" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.1" \w* \w  in the dust  |strong="776" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.2" \w* \w  of the streets .  |strong="2351" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.3" \w* \w  My young men  |strong="970" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.7" \w* \w  and maidens  |strong="1330" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.6" \w* \w  have fallen  |strong="5307" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.8" \w* \w  by the sword .  |strong="2719" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.9" \w* \w  You have slain [them]  |strong="2026" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.10" \w* \w  in the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.11" \w* \w  of Your anger ;  |strong="639" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.12" \w* \w  You have slaughtered [them]  |strong="2873" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.13" \w* \w  without  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.14" \w* \w  compassion .  |strong="2550" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.21.15" \w* \v 22 \w  You summoned  |strong="7121" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.1" \w* \w  my attackers  |strong="4032" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.4" \w* \w  on every side ,  |strong="5439" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.5" \w* \w  as for the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.2" \w* \w  of an appointed feast .  |strong="4150" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.3" \w* \w  In the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.8" \w* \w  of the LORD’s  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.10" \w* \w  anger  |strong="639" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.9" \w* \w  no  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.6" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.7" \w* \w  one escaped  |strong="6412" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.11" \w* \w  or survived ;  |strong="8300" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.12" \w* \w  my enemy  |strong="341" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.16" \w* \w  has destroyed  |strong="3615" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.17" \w* \w  those  |strong="834" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.13" \w* \w  I nurtured  |strong="2946" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.14" \w* \w  and reared .  |strong="7235" srcloc="WLC:LAM.2.22.15" \w* 
