\s The Prophet’s Afflictions
\p
\v 1 \w  I  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.1.1" \w* \f + \fr 3.1 \ft This chapter is an acrostic poem, each 3–verse stanza beginning with the successive letters of the Hebrew alphabet. \f* \w  am the man  |strong="1397" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.1.2" \w* \w  who has seen  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.1.3" \w* \w  affliction  |strong="6040" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.1.4" \w* \w  under the rod  |strong="7626" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.1.5" \w* \w  of [God’s] wrath .  |strong="5678" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.1.6" \w* \v 2 \w  He has driven me away  |strong="5090" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.2.2" \w* \w  and made me walk  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.2.3" \w* \w  in darkness  |strong="2822" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.2.4" \w* \w  instead of  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.2.5" \w* \w  light .  |strong="216" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.2.6" \w* \v 3 \w  Indeed ,  |strong="389" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.3.1" \w* \w  He keeps turning  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.3.3" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="2015" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.3.4" \w* \w  His hand  |strong="3027" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.3.5" \w* \w  against me  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.3.2" \w* \w  all day long  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.3.6" \w* \w  . . . .  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.3.7" \w* \v 4 \w  He has worn away  |strong="1086" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.4.1" \w* \w  my flesh  |strong="1320" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.4.2" \w* \w  and skin ;  |strong="5785" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.4.3" \w* \w  He has shattered  |strong="7665" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.4.4" \w* \w  my bones .  |strong="6106" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.4.5" \w* \v 5 \w  He has besieged  |strong="1129" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.5.1" \w* \w  me  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.5.2" \w* \w  and surrounded me  |strong="5362" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.5.3" \w* \w  with bitterness  |strong="7219" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.5.4" \w* \w  and hardship .  |strong="8513" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.5.5" \w* \v 6 \w  He has made me dwell  |strong="3427" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.6.2" \w* \w  in darkness  |strong="4285" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.6.1" \w* \w  like those dead  |strong="4191" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.6.3" \w* \w  for ages .  |strong="5769" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.6.4" \w* \v 7 \w  He has walled me in  |strong="1443" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.7.1" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="1157" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.7.2" \w* \w  so I cannot  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.7.3" \w* \w  escape ;  |strong="3318" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.7.4" \w* \w  He has weighed me down  |strong="3513" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.7.5" \w* \w  with chains .  |strong="5178" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.7.6" \w* \v 8 \w  Even  |strong="1571" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.8.1" \w* \w  when  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.8.2" \w* \w  I cry out  |strong="2199" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.8.3" \w* \w  and plead for help ,  |strong="7768" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.8.4" \w* \w  He shuts out  |strong="5640" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.8.5" \w* \w  my prayer .  |strong="8605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.8.6" \w* \v 9 \w  He has barred  |strong="1443" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.9.1" \w* \w  my ways  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.9.2" \w* \w  with cut stones ;  |strong="1496" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.9.3" \w* \w  He has made my paths  |strong="5410" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.9.4" \w* \w  crooked .  |strong="5753" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.9.5" \w* \v 10 \w  He  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.10.3" \w* \w   |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.10.4" \w* \w  is a bear  |strong="1677" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.10.1" \w* \w  lying in wait ,  |strong="693" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.10.2" \w* \w  a lion  |strong="738" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.10.5" \w* \w  hiding in ambush .  |strong="4565" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.10.6" \w* \v 11 \w  He forced me off  |strong="5493" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.11.2" \w* \w  my path  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.11.1" \w* \w  and tore me to pieces ;  |strong="6582" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.11.3" \w* \w  He left me  |strong="7760" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.11.4" \w* \w  without help .  |strong="8076" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.11.5" \w* \v 12 \w  He bent  |strong="1869" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.12.1" \w* \w  His bow  |strong="7198" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.12.2" \w* \w  and set me  |strong="5324" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.12.3" \w* \w  as the target  |strong="4307" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.12.4" \w* \w  for His arrow .  |strong="2671" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.12.5" \w* \v 13 \w  He pierced  |strong="935" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.13.1" \w* \w  my kidneys  |strong="3629" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.13.2" \w* \w  with His arrows  |strong="1121" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.13.3" \w* \w  . . . .  |strong="827" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.13.4" \w* \v 14 \w  I am  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.14.1" \w* \w  a laughingstock  |strong="7814" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.14.2" \w* \w  to all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.14.3" \w* \w  my people ;  |strong="5971" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.14.4" \w* \w  they mock me in song  |strong="5058" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.14.5" \w* \w  all day long  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.14.6" \w* \w  . . . .  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.14.7" \w* \v 15 \w  He has filled me  |strong="7646" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.15.1" \w* \w  with bitterness ;  |strong="4844" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.15.2" \w* \w  He has intoxicated me  |strong="7301" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.15.3" \w* \w  with wormwood .  |strong="3939" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.15.4" \w* \v 16 \w  He has ground  |strong="1638" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.16.1" \w* \w  my teeth  |strong="8127" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.16.3" \w* \w  with gravel  |strong="2687" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.16.2" \w* \w  and trampled me  |strong="3728" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.16.4" \w* \w  in the dust .  |strong="665" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.16.5" \w* \v 17 \w  My soul  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.17.3" \w* \w  has been deprived  |strong="2186" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.17.1" \w* \w  of peace ;  |strong="7965" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.17.2" \w* \w  I have forgotten  |strong="5382" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.17.4" \w* \w  what prosperity is .  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.17.5" \w* \v 18 \w  So I say ,  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.18.1" \w* \w  “ My strength  |strong="5331" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.18.3" \w* \w  has perished ,  |strong="6" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.18.2" \w* \w  along with my hope  |strong="8431" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.18.4" \w* \w  from the LORD . ”  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.18.5" \w* 
\s The Prophet’s Hope
\p
\v 19 \w  Remember  |strong="2142" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.19.1" \w* \w  my affliction  |strong="6040" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.19.2" \w* \w  and wandering ,  |strong="4788" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.19.3" \w* \w  the wormwood  |strong="3939" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.19.4" \w* \w  and the gall .  |strong="7219" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.19.5" \w* \v 20 \w  Surely  |strong="2142" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.20.1" \w* \w  my soul  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.20.5" \w* \w  remembers  |strong="2142" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.20.2" \w* \w  and is humbled  |strong="7743" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.20.3" \w* \w  within me .  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.20.4" \w* \v 21 \w  Yet I call  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.21.2" \w* \w  this  |strong="2063" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.21.1" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.21.3" \w* \w  mind ,  |strong="3820" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.21.4" \w* \w  and therefore  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.21.5" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="3651" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.21.6" \w* \w  I have hope :  |strong="3176" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.21.7" \w* \v 22 \w  Because of  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.3" \w* \w  the loving devotion  |strong="2617" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.1" \w* \f + \fr 3.22 \ft Forms of the Hebrew "chesed" are translated here and in most cases throughout the Scriptures as "loving devotion"; the range of meaning includes "love", "goodness", "kindness", "faithfulness", and "mercy", as well as "loyalty to a covenant". \f* \w  of the LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.2" \w* \w  we are not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.4" \w* \w  consumed ,  |strong="8552" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.5" \w* \w  for  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.6" \w* \w  His mercies  |strong="7356" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.9" \w* \w  never  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.7" \w* \w  fail .  |strong="3615" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.22.8" \w* \v 23 \w  They are new every morning  |strong="2319" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.23.1" \w* \w  . . . ;  |strong="1242" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.23.2" \w* \w  great  |strong="7227" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.23.3" \w* \w  is Your faithfulness !  |strong="530" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.23.4" \w* \v 24 \w  “ The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.2" \w* \w  is my portion , ”  |strong="2506" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.1" \w* \w  says  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.3" \w* \w  my soul ,  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.4" \w* \w  “ therefore  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.5" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="3651" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.6" \w* \w  I will hope  |strong="3176" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.7" \w* \w  in Him . ”  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.24.8" \w* \v 25 \w  The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.25.2" \w* \w  is good  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.25.1" \w* \w  to those who wait for Him ,  |strong="6960" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.25.3" \w* \w  to the soul  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.25.4" \w* \w  who seeks Him .  |strong="1875" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.25.5" \w* \v 26 \w  It is good  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.26.1" \w* \w  to wait  |strong="3175" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.26.2" \w* \w  quietly  |strong="1748" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.26.3" \w* \w  for the salvation  |strong="8668" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.26.4" \w* \w  of the LORD .  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.26.5" \w* \v 27 \w  It is good  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.27.1" \w* \w  for a man  |strong="1397" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.27.2" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.27.3" \w* \w  to bear  |strong="5375" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.27.4" \w* \w  the yoke  |strong="5923" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.27.5" \w* \w  while he is still young .  |strong="5271" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.27.6" \w* \v 28 \w  Let him sit  |strong="3427" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.28.1" \w* \w  alone  |strong="910" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.28.2" \w* \w  in silence ,  |strong="1826" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.28.3" \w* \w  for  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.28.4" \w* \w  God has disciplined  |strong="5190" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.28.5" \w* \w  him .  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.28.6" \w* \v 29 \w  Let him bury  |strong="5414" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.29.1" \w* \w  his face  |strong="6310" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.29.3" \w* \w  in the dust —  |strong="6083" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.29.2" \w* \w  perhaps  |strong="194" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.29.4" \w* \w  there is  |strong="3426" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.29.5" \w* \w  still hope .  |strong="8615" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.29.6" \w* \v 30 \w  Let him offer  |strong="5414" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.30.1" \w* \w  his cheek  |strong="3895" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.30.3" \w* \w  to the one who would strike him ;  |strong="5221" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.30.2" \w* \w  let him be filled  |strong="7646" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.30.4" \w* \w  with reproach .  |strong="2781" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.30.5" \w* \v 31 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.31.1" \w* \w  the Lord  |strong="136" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.31.5" \w* \w  will not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.31.2" \w* \w  cast us off  |strong="2186" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.31.3" \w* \w  forever .  |strong="5769" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.31.4" \w* \v 32 \w  Even  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.32.1" \w* \w  if  |strong="518" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.32.2" \w* \w  He causes grief ,  |strong="3013" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.32.3" \w* \w  He will show compassion  |strong="7355" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.32.4" \w* \w  according to His abundant  |strong="7230" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.32.5" \w* \w  loving devotion .  |strong="2617" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.32.6" \w* \v 33 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.33.1" \w* \w  He does not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.33.2" \w* \w  willingly  |strong="3820" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.33.4" \w* \w  afflict  |strong="6031" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.33.3" \w* \w  or grieve  |strong="3013" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.33.5" \w* \w  the sons  |strong="1121" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.33.6" \w* \w  of men .  |strong="376" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.33.7" \w* \v 34 \w  To crush  |strong="1792" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.34.1" \w* \w  underfoot  |strong="8478" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.34.2" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="7272" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.34.3" \w* \w  all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.34.4" \w* \w  the prisoners  |strong="615" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.34.5" \w* \w  of the land ,  |strong="776" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.34.6" \w* \v 35 \w  to deny  |strong="5186" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.35.1" \w* \w  a man  |strong="1397" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.35.3" \w* \w  justice  |strong="4941" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.35.2" \w* \w  before  |strong="5048" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.35.4" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.35.5" \w* \w  the Most High ,  |strong="5945" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.35.6" \w* \v 36 \w  to subvert  |strong="5791" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.36.1" \w* \w  a man  |strong="120" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.36.2" \w* \w  in his lawsuit —  |strong="7379" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.36.3" \w* \w  of these the Lord  |strong="136" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.36.4" \w* \w  does not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.36.5" \w* \w  approve .  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.36.6" \w* 
\s God’s Justice
\p
\v 37 \w  Who  |strong="4310" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.37.1" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="2088" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.37.2" \w* \w  has spoken  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.37.3" \w* \w  and it came to pass ,  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.37.4" \w* \w  unless  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.37.6" \w* \w  the Lord  |strong="136" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.37.5" \w* \w  has ordained it?  |strong="6680" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.37.7" \w* \v 38 \w  Do not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.38.3" \w* \w  both adversity  |strong="7451" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.38.5" \w* \w  and good  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.38.6" \w* \w  come  |strong="3318" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.38.4" \w* \w  from the mouth  |strong="6310" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.38.1" \w* \w  of the Most High ?  |strong="5945" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.38.2" \w* \v 39 \w  Why  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.39.1" \w* \w  should any mortal  |strong="2416" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.39.4" \w* \w  man  |strong="120" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.39.3" \w* \w  complain ,  |strong="596" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.39.2" \w* \w  in view of  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.39.6" \w* \w  [his]  |strong="1397" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.39.5" \w* \w  sins ?  |strong="2399" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.39.7" \w* \v 40 \w  Let us examine  |strong="2664" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.40.1" \w* \w  and test  |strong="2713" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.40.3" \w* \w  our ways ,  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.40.2" \w* \w  and turn back  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.40.4" \w* \w  to  |strong="5704" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.40.5" \w* \w  the LORD .  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.40.6" \w* \v 41 \w  Let us lift up  |strong="5375" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.41.1" \w* \w  our hearts  |strong="3824" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.41.2" \w* \w  and hands  |strong="3709" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.41.4" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.41.5" \w* \w  God  |strong="410" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.41.6" \w* \w  in heaven :  |strong="8064" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.41.7" \w* \v 42 \w  “ We  |strong="5168" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.42.1" \w* \w  have sinned  |strong="6586" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.42.2" \w* \w  and rebelled ;  |strong="4784" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.42.3" \w* \w  You  |strong="859" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.42.4" \w* \w  have not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.42.5" \w* \w  forgiven . ”  |strong="5545" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.42.6" \w* \v 43 \w  You have covered  |strong="5526" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.43.1" \w* \w  Yourself in anger  |strong="639" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.43.2" \w* \w  and pursued us ;  |strong="7291" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.43.3" \w* \w  You have killed  |strong="2026" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.43.4" \w* \w  without  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.43.5" \w* \w  pity .  |strong="2550" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.43.6" \w* \v 44 \w  You have covered  |strong="5526" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.44.1" \w* \w  Yourself  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.44.3" \w* \w  with a cloud  |strong="6051" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.44.2" \w* \w  that no prayer  |strong="8605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.44.5" \w* \w  can pass through .  |strong="5674" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.44.4" \w* \v 45 \w  You have made us  |strong="7760" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.45.3" \w* \w  scum  |strong="5501" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.45.1" \w* \w  and refuse  |strong="3973" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.45.2" \w* \w  among  |strong="7130" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.45.4" \w* \w  the nations .  |strong="5971" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.45.5" \w* \v 46 \w  All  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.46.4" \w* \w  our enemies  |strong="341" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.46.5" \w* \w  open  |strong="6475" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.46.1" \w* \w  their mouths  |strong="6310" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.46.3" \w* \w  against us .  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.46.2" \w* \v 47 \w  Panic  |strong="6343" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.47.1" \w* \w  and pitfall  |strong="6354" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.47.2" \w* \w  have come  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.47.3" \w* \w  upon us —  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.47.4" \w* \w  devastation  |strong="7612" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.47.5" \w* \w  and destruction .  |strong="7667" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.47.6" \w* \v 48 \w  Streams  |strong="6388" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.1" \w* \w  of tears  |strong="4325" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.2" \w* \w  flow  |strong="3381" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.3" \w* \w  from my eyes  |strong="5869" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.4" \w* \w  over  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.5" \w* \w  the destruction  |strong="7667" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.6" \w* \w  of the daughter  |strong="1323" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.7" \w* \w  of my people .  |strong="5971" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.48.8" \w* \v 49 \w  My eyes  |strong="5869" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.49.1" \w* \w  overflow  |strong="5064" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.49.2" \w* \w  unceasingly  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.49.3" \w* \w  . . . ,  |strong="1820" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.49.4" \w* \w  without  |strong="369" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.49.5" \w* \w  relief ,  |strong="2014" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.49.6" \w* \v 50 \w  until  |strong="5704" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.50.1" \w* \w  the LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.50.4" \w* \w  looks down  |strong="8259" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.50.2" \w* \w  from heaven  |strong="8064" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.50.5" \w* \w  and sees .  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.50.3" \w* \v 51 \w  My eyes  |strong="5869" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.51.1" \w* \w  bring grief  |strong="5953" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.51.2" \w* \w  to my soul  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.51.3" \w* \w  because of all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.51.4" \w* \w  the daughters  |strong="1323" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.51.5" \w* \w  of my city .  |strong="5892" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.51.6" \w* \v 52 \w  Without cause  |strong="2600" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.52.5" \w* \w  my enemies  |strong="341" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.52.4" \w* \w  hunted me  |strong="6679" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.52.1" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="6679" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.52.2" \w* \w  like a bird .  |strong="6833" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.52.3" \w* \v 53 \w  They dropped me  |strong="6789" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.53.1" \w* \w  alive  |strong="2416" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.53.3" \w* \w  into a pit  |strong="953" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.53.2" \w* \w  and cast  |strong="3034" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.53.4" \w* \w  stones  |strong="68" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.53.5" \w* \w  upon me .  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.53.6" \w* \v 54 \w  The waters  |strong="4325" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.54.2" \w* \w  flowed  |strong="6687" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.54.1" \w* \w  over  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.54.3" \w* \w  my head ,  |strong="7218" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.54.4" \w* \w  and I thought  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.54.5" \w* \w  I was going to die .  |strong="1504" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.54.6" \w* \v 55 \w  I called on  |strong="7121" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.55.1" \w* \w  Your name ,  |strong="8034" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.55.2" \w* \w  O LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.55.3" \w* \w  out of the depths  |strong="8482" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.55.5" \w* \w  of the Pit .  |strong="953" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.55.4" \w* \v 56 \w  You heard  |strong="8085" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.56.2" \w* \w  my plea :  |strong="6963" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.56.1" \w* \w  “ Do not  |strong="408" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.56.3" \w* \w  ignore  |strong="5956" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.56.4" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="241" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.56.5" \w* \w  my cry  |strong="7775" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.56.7" \w* \w  for relief . ”  |strong="7309" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.56.6" \w* \v 57 \w  You drew near  |strong="7126" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.57.1" \w* \w  when  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.57.2" \w* \w  I called on You ;  |strong="7121" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.57.3" \w* \w  You said ,  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.57.4" \w* \w  “ Do not  |strong="408" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.57.5" \w* \w  be afraid . ”  |strong="3372" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.57.6" \w* \v 58 \w  You defend  |strong="7378" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.58.1" \w* \w  my  |strong="5315" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.58.4" \w* \w  cause ,  |strong="7379" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.58.3" \w* \w  O Lord ;  |strong="136" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.58.2" \w* \w  You redeem  |strong="1350" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.58.5" \w* \w  my life .  |strong="2416" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.58.6" \w* \v 59 \w  You have seen ,  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.59.1" \w* \w  O LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.59.2" \w* \w  the wrong done to me ;  |strong="5792" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.59.3" \w* \w  vindicate  |strong="8199" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.59.4" \w* \w  my cause !  |strong="4941" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.59.5" \w* \v 60 \w  You have seen  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.60.1" \w* \w  all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.60.2" \w* \w  their malice ,  |strong="5360" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.60.3" \w* \w  all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.60.4" \w* \w  their plots  |strong="4284" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.60.5" \w* \w  against me .  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.60.6" \w* \v 61 \w  O LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.61.3" \w* \w  You have heard  |strong="8085" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.61.1" \w* \w  their insults ,  |strong="2781" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.61.2" \w* \w  all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.61.4" \w* \w  their plots  |strong="4284" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.61.5" \w* \w  against me —  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.61.6" \w* \v 62 \w  the slander  |strong="8193" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.62.1" \w* \w  and murmuring  |strong="1902" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.62.3" \w* \w  of my assailants  |strong="6965" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.62.2" \w* \w  against me  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.62.4" \w* \w  all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.62.5" \w* \w  day long .  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.62.6" \w* \v 63 \w  When they sit  |strong="7675" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.63.1" \w* \w  and when they rise ,  |strong="7012" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.63.2" \w* \w  see how  |strong="5027" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.63.3" \w* \w  vvv  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.63.4" \w* \w  they mock me in song .  |strong="4485" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.63.5" \w* \v 64 \w  You will pay them back  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.64.1" \w* \w   |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.64.2" \w* \w  what they deserve ,  |strong="1576" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.64.3" \w* \w  O LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.64.4" \w* \w  according to the work  |strong="4639" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.64.5" \w* \w  of their hands .  |strong="3027" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.64.6" \w* \v 65 \w  Put  |strong="5414" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.65.1" \w* \w  a veil of anguish  |strong="4044" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.65.3" \w* \w  over their hearts ;  |strong="3820" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.65.4" \w* \w  may Your curse be  |strong="8381" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.65.5" \w* \w  upon them !  |srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.65.6" \w* \v 66 \w  You will pursue them  |strong="7291" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.66.1" \w* \w  in anger  |strong="639" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.66.2" \w* \w  and exterminate them  |strong="8045" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.66.3" \w* \w  from under  |strong="8478" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.66.4" \w* \w  [Your] heavens ,  |strong="8064" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.66.5" \w* \w  O LORD .  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:LAM.3.66.6" \w* 
